
Form Handling
     1. Controlled  : Where Form Data is Handled by React Component State
     2. UnControlled : Where Form Data is Handled by DOM itself
     3. React-Hook-Form : third party Library (hybrid: controlled and uncontrolled)

Zod And Yup Schema Validations:

Key Differences to Remember:

Feature	                            Yup	                                    Zod
Import	                    import * as yup from "yup"	            import * as z from "zod"
Schema creation	             yup.object()	                            z.object()
String validation	        yup.string().required()	                z.string() (required by default)
Number validation	        yup.number().required()	                z.number() (required by default)
Regex validation	        .matches(/[A-Z]/, "message")	          .regex(/[A-Z]/, "message")
Type inference	            Manual interface needed	                   z.infer<typeof schema>
Required fields	            Explicit .required()	                Implicit (all fields required by default)



.matches(/[A-Z]/, "Password must contain at least one uppercase letter")
.matches(/[a-z]/, "Password must contain at least one lowercase letter")
.matches(/[0-9]/, "Password must contain at least one digit")
.matches(/[@$!%*?&#]/, "Password must contain at least one special character"), 


.matches(/^\d+$/, "Phone number must contain only digits")


